    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved pot to a medium heat with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>flour </strong>and stir for 1-2 min or until a sandy paste forms – this is your <strong>roux</strong></p><p>Gradually add 200ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[300ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[400ml]</span> <strong>milk</strong> into the roux<strong> </strong>with your <strong>soft cheese </strong>and whisk for 3-4 min or until a smooth, thick sauce remains</p>",
